`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The graph validation builds a `Set<string>` of all `nodeId`s in O(n) then checks each branch's `targetNodeId` in O(1). This keeps validation linear in nodes+branches — safe even for large trees. Terminal nodes (empty `branches: []`) are inherently valid and need no special case.
